latestIgtvVideos.title: How do I keep my skin healthy from inside out .
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
SKIN CARE ROUTINE: Now I do use good  skincare products with powerful ingredients and follow my skincare routine religiously - vitamin c serum, retinol and SPF are my essentials. I love face masks too! 

WORKOUT: Nothing beats the impact of eating well and following a consistent workout routine. Your internal mental and physical well being will always reflect on your skin/hair. Besides, who doesn’t like that facial glow after a good workout session?!
 
GOOD FOOD: Our simple Indian wholesome foods work the best. You don’t need to go after fancy foods all the time; maybe sometimes if you like - like I do eat salmon/kale /tempeh /blueberries occasionally. I replace refined/processed foods with natural foods as much as possible. Just combine your daily food well & follow portion control. Also, I never shy away from healthy fats. Desi Ghee is a must! 

HYDRATE: We know it, but we don’t do it. Just measure your daily intake and keep a target for yourself. I like to infuse water with floral herbs/fruits/spices. I also drink 2 cups of matcha tea a day. 

SUPPLEMENTS: good quality supplements do help (but they are not a replacement for nutrient intake from natural foods). I take liposomal vitamin c, collagen peptides, probiotics and omegas regularly. 

GOOD SLEEP: restful sleep will keep puffy eyes & dark circles at bay. It’s a must for a glowing, happy & healthy skin.

That’s it from my end. Feel free to add to the list! ☺️

latestPosts.caption:
HABIT STACKING: Learned about this fascinating concept in the book “Atomic Habits”, and applied it to my routine. I had been meaning to read more and read regularly, but found myself putting it away for other priorities. A friend insisted I read this book, and I found it useful! 

What is it? Building new habits into our daily lives by stacking them onto already established habits. I keep a book on every side table that I access during the day. Whenever I sink down on the couch with my phone for some mindless scrolling, I grab my book on the side table instead. I have stacked up another habit i.e. as soon as I pick up the book to read, I place a glass of water alongside, so I can increase my water intake. The idea is to do this chain of events repeatedly, so that it all stacks up into a small routine! Quite cool, no? What do you think?

SHAKTI 🌺

I always feel at peace when I visit a sacred pilgrimage. But my visit to Maa Kamakhya’s temple in Guwahati (a Shakti Peeth) last month hit me differently. In fact, I felt it was the other way around – She called me to Her. Instead of the usual feelings of peace and quiet, I actually felt a kind of adrenaline rush in my body. It was magnetic, so much so that I felt high on that energy for several days after my visit. It is rare to feel such movement of vibrations at one spot. It’s because She is the Shakti that nurtures the seed and brings it to fruition. And now she resides in my heart. Jai Maa Kamakhya 🙏🏻🌺 The Divine Feminine 🌸

latestPosts.caption:
This one is for my followers who love all things traditional and old school (just like I do), I wore my grandmother’s lehenga for my cousin’s wedding – a piece that is over 100 years old and holds immense sentimental value for me. It is a lightweight garment, not heavily embroidered, unlike many traditional pieces. 

This cherished lehenga underwent a beautiful restoration by @saurabrajeshwari , known for reviving old-world craftsmanship and making their own beautiful creations too. They did such an amazing job! The intricate work features real silver and gold, which was all immaculately finished. 
So thankful for their dedication to preserving the beauty of my heritage. ♥️✨

Serum Spotlight! These are a few vitamin C serums I personally swear by, all available in India! 
1. @elizabetharden Vitamin C Ceramide Capsules - These little capsules deliver a powerful brightening effect while nourishing my skin barrier. Perfect for that radiant glow! Women with dry skin will love this one. If you have oily combination skin then go for one capsule. 
2. @zoskinhealth_india Self-Activating 10% Vitamin C - Though exclusively available through dermatologists and clinics, this serum is worth trying. It works wonders for evening out my skin tone and gives my complexion a healthy boost. Perfect for summer months. 
3. @obagimedical Professional C Peptide Complex - This powerhouse not only brightens but also fights signs of aging with its peptide blend, keeping my skin looking fresh and vibrant. 
Has anyone tried these serums? 

#SkincareFavorites #VitamincSerum  #GlowGoals

Looking for a nutritious vegetarian meal? Give this a try! I added tofu to my bharta for a protein boost, and it pairs perfectly with fiber-rich roti made from khapli atta. I enriched the dough with cooked puréed sprout dal, a touch of green chili, pink salt, and a dash of A2 ghee for extra flavor and healthy fats. On the side, I enjoyed a simple salad of cucumber, cherry tomatoes, lettuce, and celery dressed with lemon juice, black pepper and pink salt — such a refreshing complement! 
This combo not only tastes incredible but also keeps me feeling full and energized! 🍆🥗 
How do you love to enjoy your veggies? What’s your go-to veggie dish? Share below! 👇💬 #HealthyEating #PlantBasedDelights #WholesomeGoodness #VeggiePower

Just made this delicious black chickpea salad that’s a staple in our home! With 1 cup of overnight soaked black chickpeas cooked the next day. I tossed in fresh cherry tomatoes, crunchy chopped celery, creamy avocado, green onions and a hint of green chili (optional for a bit of zing!). 
The real magic is in the dressing—a blend of freshly squeezed orange juice, a garlic clove, crushed black pepper, a splash of virgin olive oil, and a sprinkle of pink salt, all whisked together for a burst of flavor! Can’t wait to enjoy this refreshing, nutritious bowl of goodness! 😋

#HomeCooking #HealthySalad #Deliciousness

I’m currently obsessed with the @isdin.india Retinal Intense after finishing the @isclinical_india Retinol + Emulsion 1.0 🌟 These products have truly changed the game for me, packed with powerful ingredients that really deliver results. My skin has adjusted so well to the higher-strength retinols, and I can actually see the difference in texture!
But here’s a friendly reminder: the golden rule is to KNOW YOUR SKIN! 🧖‍♀️ Taking the time to understand your unique skin type is so important when choosing the right retinol strength. And never hesitate to chat with your dermatologist for personalized advice—finding that perfect match will make all the difference and please don’t forget to use your SPF in the day!!
